ISSUES:
H|undefined-reference|framework/claude/settings.json:6|`sdd-review-self-ext` has a shipped skill definition, but `settings.json` does not grant `Skill(sdd-review-self-ext)`. After install, the skill is present under `.claude/skills/` yet blocked by permissions, so the external self-review entrypoint is unreachable.
H|protocol-inconsistency|framework/claude/skills/sdd-roadmap/refs/review.md:5|The canonical review ref still declares `review design|impl {feature}` as the trigger and parser contract, while the router explicitly supports `review design --cross-check`, `review impl --cross-check`, `review design --wave N`, and `review impl --wave N` without a feature operand. This leaves the router→ref handoff ambiguous and makes the feature-less review modes internally inconsistent.
M|unreachable-path|framework/claude/skills/sdd-roadmap/refs/review.md:137|`review.md` documents a cross-cutting verdict path at `specs/.cross-cutting/{id}/verdicts.md`, and `refs/revise.md` Step 8 says to persist there, but the review execution flow never defines a cross-cutting scope directory or invocation path. The destination exists only as documentation, so cross-cutting review archival is underspecified.
M|protocol-inconsistency|framework/claude/skills/sdd-reboot/refs/reboot.md:194|Phase 7 allows `skip` on design-review exhaustion and explicitly excludes skipped specs from the wave EXIT condition, but the later Completion Condition still requires all specs to have `design-generated` plus GO/CONDITIONAL verdicts. Those two rules cannot both be true, so the skip branch has no consistent completion criterion.
